name: uk-civil-service-yearbook
notes:
Discussed at [Workshop on Public Information, 2008-11-02](http://okfn.org/wiki/PublicInformation).

The Civil Service Yearbook apparently contains interesting statistics and information. From the [website](http://www.civil-service.co.uk/):

> WELCOME to the Official online directory for all government departments, executive agencies and related organisations. You can search the directory for departmental addresses and telephone numbers and view civil service salary scales and statistical data, or as a subscriber you can access all levels of the database including organisational structures, employee names and contact details. 

From the [Copyright notice](http://www.civil-service.co.uk/pages/copyright.asp):

> Â© Crown Copyright 2008. All rights reserved.

> The Civil Service Year Book is a value-added product. Applications to reproduce any of the content should be made in writing to: Office of Public Sector Information, Information Policy Division, St Clements House, 2-16 Colegate, Norwich, NR3 BQ.
